  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Indentifying the significant figures in a given number</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>How many significant figures are there in the following masses?</p>
<p>(a) \({@first_number@}\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]</p>
<p>(b) \({@second_number@}\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]][[feedback:prt2]]</p>
<p>(c) \({@third_number@}\) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]][[feedback:prt3]]</p>
<p>(d) \({@fourth_number@}\) [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]][[feedback:prt4]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked solution</h3>
<p>Part a: {@first_number@}</p>
<p>All nonzero digits are significant.</p>
<p>Thus, {@first_number@} has \(5\) significant figures.</p>
<p>Part b: {@second_number@}</p>
<p>Leading zeros (to the left of the first nonzero digit) are not significant.
</p>
<p>Therefore, {@second_number@} has \(2\) significant figures.</p>
<p>Part c:  {@third_number@}</p>
<p>All zeros between nonzero digits are significant.</p>
<p>Therefore, {@third_number@} has \(6\) significant figures.</p>
<p></p>
<p>Part d:  {@fourth_number@}</p>
<p>Trailing zeros to the right of the decimal place are significant.</p>
<p>Therefore, {@fourth_number@} has {@ta4@} significant figures.</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
